http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/Handri-Neeva-project/article14019288.ece

Minister for Environment and Forest Bojjala Gopalakrishna Reddy formally launched the Kuppam sub-canal work, which is part of the Handri Neeva Sujala Sravanthi (HNSS) project, on Sunday. Participating in the ‘Bhumi Puja’ performed for the Rs. 468 crore-project at Appinapalli in Peddapanjani mandal of Chittoor district, the Minister announced that all tanks in Chittoor district would get water shortly, as envisaged by chief minister N. Chandrababu Naidu.The State’s effort to desilt the tank beds got support from nature in the form of heavy rains, which helped in water storage, he added.Collector Siddharth Jain announced supply of water to all farmers in the region by completing the HNSS project in time, as three Deputy Collectors had been drafted for the purpose. He appealed to farmers to offer their lands voluntarily for the prestigious project, as was the case with those ryots who surrendered their lands for the establishment of IIT, IISER and international airport.